<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>She hated having visitors in the house while <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="her health was so indifferent"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(她身体不好时)</code></b>, and lovers were of all people the most disagreeable.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Kitty and Lydia were <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="far from [doing something]"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(丝毫不)</code></b> envying Miss Lucas, for Mr. Collins was only a clergyman, and it affected them in no other way than as a piece of news to spread at Meryton.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Her disappointment in Charlotte made her <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="turn with fonder regard to her sister"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(转而对姐姐更加关心和喜爱)</code></b>, of whose rectitude and delicacy she was sure her opinion could never be shaken, and for whose happiness she grew daily more anxious, as Bingley had now been gone a week, and nothing was heard of his return.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>After <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="discharging his conscience"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(表达他的歉意)</code></b> on that head, he proceeded to inform them, with many rapturous expressions, of his happiness in having obtained the affection of their amiable neighbor, Miss Lucas, and then explained that it was merely with the view of enjoying her <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="society"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(交往)</code></b> that he had been so ready to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="close with"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(同意/达成一致)</code></b> their kind wish of seeing him again at Lougbourn.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Day after day passed away without bringing any other <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="tidings"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(消息)</code></b> of him than the report which shortly prevailed in Meryton of his coming no more to Netherfield the whole winter, a report which highly incensed Mrs. Bennet, and which she never failed to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="contradict as a most scandalous falsehood"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(反驳说是最可耻的谎言)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Lady Lucas could <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="not be insensible of triumph"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(必然感到得意[双重否定])</code></b> on being able to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="retort on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(回敬/报复)</code></b> Mrs. Bennet the comfort of having a daughter well married.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="The chief of every day was spent"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(每天大部分的时间都用在...上)</code></b> by him at Lucas Lodge.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
